cards.title: Your EGO Power+ Blower and $85 Card Are Coming From Lowes

descriptionBlocks.text:
Email de: Lowe's Tool SpeciaI <LowesToolSpeciaI@diseylatino.com>

Thanks for checking on the plan for next week.
On Tuesday I can join after lunch, but I’ll need a heads-up about the room setup because I’m bringing the sample boards.
If you want the agenda tightened, I’d put the quick updates first, then decisions, then the open items at the end so we don’t drift.
For the notes, I can capture action items as we go, but I’ll need someone to confirm owners before we wrap up.
About the checklist you asked for: yes, I can share the version I used last time, but tell me whether we’re keeping the same timeline.
Also, if you’re still deciding between two options, send me the pros/cons you already have and I’ll organize them into a simple compare list.
Let me know if Thursday is better; I can adjust.
LOWE'S
Customer follow-up

1-minute questionnaire: receive an EGO Power+ Leaf Blower + $85 Store Card
You're receiving this because you've shopped at Lowe's before. Share a quick note about your recent experience—most people finish in a minute or less.
Details

Account ID:
LW-4821-9930 Check-in code:
QX7P-1M Estimated time:
Under 1 minute Status:
Not completed

EGO Power+ Leaf Blower details
• Lightweight design for everyday yard cleanups
• Variable speed control for edging, patios, and driveways
• High air volume and strong airflow for moving leaves and debris
• Quiet operation compared with many gas models

Get the EGO Blower + $85 Store Card


Note: This message is intended for a past Lowe's shopper and references the details shown above. Please keep your Account ID and Check-in code for your records.

Lowe's customer experience team

© Lowe's. All rights reserved.

Yes, I can handle the schedule you asked about.
If we keep it simple, I’d suggest meeting for a short block and leaving a buffer afterward for follow-ups.
For the location, the quieter corner works better because it’s easier to hear everyone on the call.
About the food question: I’m fine with anything, but it helps if there’s at least one option without dairy, just in case someone needs it.
If you’re wondering whether to bring printed handouts, I’d skip them and send a single document link instead so the latest version is always the one people use.
I can also draft a quick reminder message the day before, focusing on what to bring and what decisions we need to make.
Tell me which day you prefer and I’ll adjust my calendar.
